## Security Architecture

### Secret Handling Model

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ SECRETVAULT MASTER KEY (Root-Only, Immutable)              │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ File: /etc/little7/secretvault_master.key                  │
│ Perms: 0600 (root:root)                                    │
│ Size: 64 hex characters (256-bit random)                   │
│ Source: openssl rand -hex 32 (Stage 20)                    │
│ Access: sudo only (no regular user access)                 │
│ Audit: /var/log/audit/audit.log (auditd)                   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                            │
                ┌───────────┼───────────┐
                ▼           ▼           ▼
        ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐
        │ Stage 21     │ │ openclaw-    │ │ Other        │
        │ (Seed API    │ │ start        │ │ services     │
        │ Keys)        │ │ (Runtime     │ │ (if needed)  │
        │              │ │ injection)   │ │              │
        └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ SECRET INJECTION PATTERNS                                   │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ 1. SETUP (Stage 21):                                        │
│    • Read master key from 0600 file                         │
│    • Store in temp file (0600)                              │
│    • Pass via FD or subshell (NOT command-line)             │
│    • Secure wipe: shred -vfz -n 5                           │
│                                                              │
│ 2. RUNTIME (openclaw-start):                                │
│    • Query SecretVault using master key                     │
│    • Receive grant file path (encrypted, time-limited)      │
│    • Read API key from grant file (just-in-time)            │
│    • Exec with clean env: env -i [minimal vars] ...         │
│    • Core dumps disabled: ulimit -c 0                       │
│                                                              │
│ 3. AUDIT:                                                   │
│    • All access logged to /var/log/audit/                   │
│    • Monitoring: auditctl -w /etc/little7/ -p wa -k ...     │
│    • Alerts: Systemd journal forwarding to syslog            │
│                                                              │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Privilege Escalation Boundaries

```
SETUP PHASE (Installer):
├─ sudo apt-get update           ✅ (System package manager)
├─ sudo apt-get install          ✅ (System packages)
├─ sudo mkdir -p /opt/little7    ✅ (System directories)
├─ sudo chmod 700 /etc/...       ✅ (Hardened perms)
├─ sudo useradd unifai-operator  ✅ (Service principal)
├─ sudo systemctl enable         ✅ (Init system)
└─ sudo docker-compose up        ✅ (Container start)

RUNTIME PHASE (Service User):
├─ docker-compose ps             ✅ (User in docker group)
├─ supervisord                   ✅ (Service principal)
├─ openclaw-start                ✅ (Service principal)
└─ Log rotation (systemd)        ✅ (systemd-logind)

AUDIT PHASE (Root):
├─ /var/log/audit/audit.log      ✅ (Audit daemon)
├─ journalctl -xe                ✅ (Root review)
└─ Security scanning             ✅ (Compliance tools)
```

