## Running the Refactored Installer

### Quick Start (All Stages)

```bash
cd /home/wilgner/UnifAI/unifai_repo/little7-installer

# 1. Verify lock file and all checksums
./install.sh verify

# 2. Run all stages with pinned artifacts
./install.sh all

# 3. Run specific stage (e.g., Stage 21)
./install.sh 21

# 4. Run by number (matches any stage 21_*)
./install.sh 21
```

### Secure Secrets Injection

```bash
# 1. Create secure .env file
cp .env.example .env.local
chmod 0600 .env.local
nano .env.local     # Edit with your API keys

# 2. Source and run Stage 21
source .env.local
./install.sh 21

# 3. Verify SecretVault
node /opt/little7/supervisor/supervisor-secretvault/src/cli.js list \
  --alias codex-oauth

# 4. Secure cleanup
shred -vfz -n 5 .env.local
```

### Controlled Refresh (Update Pinned Versions)

```bash
# Re-pin dependencies against latest remote versions
LITTLE7_REFRESH_BOOTSTRAP=1 ./install.sh 00
LITTLE7_REFRESH_BOOTSTRAP=1 ./install.sh 20
LITTLE7_REFRESH_BOOTSTRAP=1 ./install.sh 50

# New lock values are computed; verify before committing
git diff config/bootstrap-config.lock
git add config/bootstrap-config.lock
git commit -m "chore: refresh bootstrap lock with latest pinned versions"
```

